      "content": "If the symptoms are gone, that's a sign the initial battle is won, but you still need to finish the full course to ensure every last bit of the infection is eradicated and to prevent any lingering issues. Stopping prematurely is the fastest way to invite a relapse, and your liver and kidneys are built to handle this kind of necessary treatment. For a complete, lasting cure, stick to the prescribed schedule until the doctor gives the all-clear.",
      "source": "target",
